#: ../../W/wabbit.rst:5
msgid "wabbit"
msgstr "wabbit"

#: ../../W/wabbit.rst:7
msgid "/wab´it/, n\\."
msgstr "/wab´it/, 名詞"

#: ../../W/wabbit.rst:9
msgid ""
"[almost certainly from Elmer Fudd's immortal line \"You wascawwy wabbit!\"]"
msgstr "[ほぼ確実に、Elmer Fuddの不朽の台詞\"You wascawwy wabbit!\"から]"

#: ../../W/wabbit.rst:12
msgid ""
"A legendary early hack reported on a System/360 at RPI and elsewhere around "
"1978; this may have descended (if only by inspiration) from a hack called "
"RABBITS reported from 1969 on a Burroughs 5500 at the University of "
"Washington Computer Center. The program would make two copies of itself "
"every time it was run, eventually crashing the system."
msgstr ""
"1978年頃にRPIなどでSystem/360上で報告された伝説的な初期のハック。これは1969年にWashington大学コンピュータセンターのBurroughs"
" "
"5500上で報告されたRABBITSというハックから(着想だけにせよ)派生したのかもしれない。このプログラムは実行されるたびに自分自身のコピーを二つ作り、最終的にはシステムをクラッシュさせた。"

#: ../../W/wabbit.rst:16
msgid ""
"By extension, any hack that includes infinite self-replication but is not a "
":ref:`virus` or :ref:`worm`\\. See :ref:`fork-bomb` and :ref:`rabbit-job`\\,"
" see also :ref:`cookie-monster`\\."
msgstr ""
"拡張して、無限の自己複製を含むが\\ :ref:`virus`\\ でも\\ :ref:`worm`\\ でもないあらゆるハック。\\ "
":ref:`fork-bomb`\\ と\\ :ref:`rabbit-job`\\ を参照。\\ :ref:`cookie-monster`\\ "
"も参照。"
